Smart Timetable Generator
 
## Problem Statement
Manual timetable creation is time-consuming and often results in scheduling conflicts.

## Solution
This system generates an automated timetable based on subject credits and teacher availability while avoiding conflicts.
If subject credits are not available, the system uses fixed weekly subject allocation or balanced distribution to generate the timetable

## Features
- Credit-based subject allocation
-Fixed Period Allocation
- Equal Distribution(if no credits)
- Teacher availability constraints
- Conflict-free scheduling
- Balanced weekly distribution

## Tech Stack
- Python
- Data Structures
- (Optional) Flask for web interface
